    "---\n",
    "## Section 6 — v6: Class Balancing\n",
    "\n",
    "**Motivation:** v5 (commit 02875ac, 2026-03-18) activated the 5 fundamental features\n",
    "for the standard pool and retrained both models. Results showed a strong **UP bias** in both pools:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Pool | Model | Accuracy | UP recall | DOWN recall |\n",
    "|---|---|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Standard | GBC | 51.55% | 0.93 | 0.35 |\n",
    "| Fallback | GBC | 55.68% | 0.93 | 0.11 |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Root cause:** Stock markets trended upward over 2020-2024 (~52% of training days are UP).\n",
    "Tree ensembles (GBC, RF) exploit this structural imbalance by defaulting toward UP predictions.\n",
    "DOWN recall near 0.11 means the fallback model almost never issues a meaningful SELL signal.\n",
    "\n",
    "**v6 fix — balanced class weights across all classifiers:**\n",
    "\n",
    "| Classifier | Mechanism |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| `LogisticRegression` | `class_weight='balanced'` (already set in v5) |\n",
    "| `RandomForestClassifier` | `class_weight='balanced'` added |\n",
    "| `GradientBoostingClassifier` | `sample_weight=compute_sample_weight('balanced', y_train)` in `.fit()` |\n",
    "| `LGBMClassifier` | `is_unbalance=True` added |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Expected effect:** Overall accuracy may drop slightly (model no longer exploits the UP\n",
    "frequency shortcut) but DOWN recall should improve substantially, producing meaningful SELL\n",
    "signals. `LogisticRegression` with `class_weight='balanced'` and C selected by\n",
    "`TimeSeriesSplit` CV is expected to become the winning model.\n"
   ]
  },
